Slurm

```json
{
  "application": "Slurm",
  "resource_requirements": {
    "job_name": "stats",
    "output_file": "0_stats_real_log/%x_%j.out",
    "error_file": "0_stats_real_log/%x_%j.err",
    "memory": "10G",
    "time": "0:30:00",
    "partition": "cpu-short",
    "tasks": 1,
    "conda_env": "/home/s2358093/data1/conda_envs/hvm-05",
    "python_version": "python --version",
    "environment_variables": [
      "LD_LIBRARY_PATH=$ENV/lib:$LD_LIBRARY_PATH:$CONDA_PREFIX/lib/"
    ]
  },
  "script": "stats.py"
}
```

This script utilizes the Slurm workload manager for resource allocation and job management. It specifies the job name, output and error file paths, memory requirements, execution time, partition, and number of tasks. It also sets up a conda environment (hvm-05) and defines the path for the LD_LIBRARY_PATH environment variable. The script then executes a Python script named "stats.py".
